		"body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThis PR adds a feedback message in the master password dialog when the two entered passwords do not match.\r\n\r\nPreviously, only the invalid icon was displayed when the passwords differed. This change improves user feedback by showing a clear message: \"Passwords do not match\".\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- Added a conditional message below the password fields when the entered passwords do not match.\r\n- The message is shown only when the second password field has input and the passwords differ.\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n\r\n1. Open **Tools → Options → Encryption → Manage master password**\r\n2. Enter a password in the \"Enter password\" field\r\n3. Enter a different value in the \"Re-enter password\" field\r\n4. Verify that the message **\"Passwords do not match\"** appears below the field\r\n<img width=\"781\" height=\"663\" alt=\"Password-mismatch\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d03d886f-47a1-4475-933a-fcd749d0e3e1\" />\r\n",
